body:
@sirpkt @navis new approach looks good to me. 
@fjy no perf needed with the latest updates.

@sirpkt pls rebase/squash and fix conflicts.

@drcrallen I'm fine calling it experimental.
sounds like high level approach is ok.
@pjain1 can you make necessary add/updates and remove the "Discuss" when done?

In that case the query would look like:

``` json
{
  "queryType": "timeseries",
  "dataSource": "wikipedia",
  "granularity": "all",
  "intervals": [
    "2016-02-01/2016-02-05"
  ],
  "aggregations": [
    {
      "fieldNames": [
        "page"
      ],
      "name": "NumPages",
      "type": "cardinality"
    }
  ],
  "postAggregations": [
    {
      "type": "finalizeFieldAccess",
      "name": "NumPages",
      "fieldName": "NumPagesFinal"
    },
    {
      "type": "javascript",
      "name": "NumPagesMod1337",
      "fieldNames": [
        "NumPagesFinal"
      ],
      "function": "function(NumPagesFinal) { return NumPagesFinal % 1337 }"
    }
  ]
}
```
